HEADWORD: Polypodium
<hw>Pol"y*po`di*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/, dim. of <?/. See <er>Polyp</er>, and cf. 2d
<er>Polypode</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of plants of
the order <ord>Filices</ord> or ferns. The fructifications are in
uncovered roundish points, called <xex>sori</xex>, scattered over the
inferior surface of the frond or leaf. There are numerous
species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

